    "body": "### Problem\n\nHalf the issue a plugin like [Harpoon](https://github.com/ThePrimeagen/harpoon) solves is that global marks don't update their position to where the cursor last was before we left that file. This can be trivially solved with an autocommand like below:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"BufLeave\", \"VimLeavePre\" }, {\n        desc = \"Update global marks automatically\",\n        callback = function()\n                local lnum, col = unpack(vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0))\n                local ascii_A = 65\n                local ascii_Z = 90\n                for i = ascii_A, ascii_Z do\n                        local mark = string.char(i)\n                        local row = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_mark(0, mark)[1]\n                        if row ~= 0 then vim.api.nvim_buf_set_mark(0, mark, lnum, col, {}) end\n                end\n        end,\n})\n```\n\nThis bad boy saw some changes when I realized I didn't need to use `vim.fn.getmarklist()` and pattern match its output, but I've been using this for over a year now and can confirm it replaces my use case for harpoon.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nGlobal marks update themselves.",
