            "body": "There are some interesting Harpoon concepts discussed at https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/36329 \n\nbut I don't quite understand this: \n\n> global marks don't update their position to where the cursor last was before we left that file\n\nmarks (global or otherwise) are intended to store a precise position. Why would we assume that all global marks should be changed? A single file might have multiple global marks.\n\nIt sounds like `:args` may fit your use-case better, and as mentioned in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/36329 , we would welcome a design proposal.",
